  Title: God in All Worlds
  Locus:
    Page: 70
  Source:
    Title: Answer to Job
By: C. G. Jung
---
The enlightened person remains what he is, and is never more than his own
limited ego before the One who dwells within him, whose form has no knowable
boundaries, who encompasses him on all sides, fathomless as the abysms of
the earth and vast as the sky.
